args: Leif came to deliver Chelle a letter. But just as he\nwas about to leave, Chelle suddenly stopped him...
Is something the matter, Lady Chelle?
(Making an excuse now would be\nutterly disgraceful.)
(But nor can I allow this awkward silence\nto persist...)
Ahem. It is nothing.\nYou should hurry back at once.
(This is the only option I have.)
I have decided that I will stay in this town\nfor the night.
Prince Leonidas urged me to occasionally\nallow myself a bit of leisure, you see.
If I were to return now, I would be acting\nin direct opposition to his words.
So you have to be ordered to enjoy\nyourself. How very in-character for you.
(Here I'd thought he'd seen through me,\nbut I suppose that's never something I\nneed concern myself with around Leif.)
Then you'll be accompanying me on\na stroll along the shore this evening.\nDo I make myself clear?
Crystal, my lady. I shall come to fetch you\nlater tonight.
Of course. Goodness, the beach at night\nis so quiet. All the good children are in\nbed, leaving this place for us adults.
Indeed. You can hear the waves so clearly.
I know prevarication is a lost cause on\nyou, so I will get straight to the point.
Why did you decide to stay the night?

I know you were planning to leave right
away. Is the reason you changed your
plans because I so uncharacteristically
blurted out that I wanted you to wait?
It was terribly childish of me. I cannot\nunderstand why I let myself do that.
I am a full-grown adult. I have to restrain\nmyself from such impulsive outbursts.
Yet it was that request that convinced me\nto tarry here.
I could tell that it was what you wanted in\nyour heart. It has been some time since I\nhave heard you speak your true feelings.
It made me remember how, when you\nwere young, you wept and begged me\nto go to the beach with you.
I-I cannot say I recall that myself.\nHonestly, you should wipe that memory\nfrom your mind.
I remember it clearly. There was a time\nwhen even you were childlike and candid\nabout your feelings.
That is why I worry about you sometimes.
You've grown. Or rather, to put it more\nprecisely, you were forced to grow up.
That's right. It's only natural for those in\na position of power. A lady cannot guide\nher people if she is mired in naiveté.
I find that attitude quite admirable.\nBut I would urge you to find time\nto be yourself on occasion as well.

If you could allow yourself to return to
those innocent days once more, even if
only for a short time...I truly believe it
would be to your benefit.
Then... Could that include asking you to\nspoil me for the night?
If that is what you wish.
I am here to serve you and the kingdom of\nAlberia. I will do whatever you ask of me.
No matter what happens,\nI will always be at your side.
Honestly, you are just so... Rrgh.

I feel there are a few lessons you could
learn from me as well. For instance,
you could maybe learn to read between
the lines.
You're a grown man yourself, so surely\nyou can try to understand these things.
Lady Chelle! You mustn't run off on your\nown!
(Coded language does not work on Leif,\nso I no longer need it.)

(I have decided that when I am with him,
I will let myself return to the halcyon days
of girlhood...and be honest about how I
truly feel.)
Oh, quit your fussing. This is a vacation,\nso we should make the most of it!
I have a knight here I can depend on.\nShouldn't that leave me free to relax?
I'd say this is going to make for\none mewtiful memory.
Now there really is nothing more\nshe could want this summer.
The night is still young, dear Leif.\nMy fun is only just getting started!
